==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Funky
<hw>Funk"y</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧⟦nsm⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, or characterized by, great fear, or funking; having
great fear.</def> <mark>[Colloq. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Funky</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Funky
<hw>Funk"y</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧⟦nsm⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>having
an earthy, unsophisticated style or feeling;</def> <specif>in</specif>
<fld>(Music)</fld>, <def>earthy and seemingly unsophisticated, having
elements of black American blues and gospel. See 2nd <er>funk</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Funnel</ent>⟦br⟧
